data:
The State Comprehensive School "Papa Giovanni XXIII", including nine school buildings, three pre-primary schools, three primary schools and three lower secondary schools, located on two neighboring municipalities in a rural area of the province of Pescara , is engaged in a broad scheme of development  and modernization. It has placed among its medium-term targets the creation of a systemic self-assessment tool, aimed at providing accountability to all stakeholders.



The opportunity provided by KA1 - Mobility of school staff - Erasmus + allows us to extend the comparison and analysis of good practices  in order to increase levels of education through effective " leadership for learning ",  in a context where the management style of the headteacher  and the " middle management " have to be settled.

Since Italy does not have codified rules for the allocation of responsibilities within the staff, nor  an external or internal assessment system, we believe that  the  direct observation of school management and evaluation system in countries that have a long  tradition of  consolidated school autonomy  can be useful, although being aware of the significant differences in cultural and regulatory environment .

The experience may have an impact not only local, but also regional and national.

In fact the Institute enjoys a privileged position because it leads some networks of schools in activities  of action-research in several topics, in order to improve the organization and drive educational innovation . The headteacher  is also part of some regional groups where she is able to work systematically with important educational decision-makers at a local, regional, national level.



The Headteacher, the Deputy  Headteacher,  three teachers (one from pre-primay, one  from primary and one from lower secondary   school) from the Italian Institute participate in JOB SHADOWING activities at school of the Anglo-Saxon area: Anchorsholme Academy in Blackpool, England and Carlow Educate Together in Carlow, Ireland.

The aim of the activity focus on  management and on the assessment  system, through:

1 . DIRECT OBSERVATION OF THE ACTIVITIES OF THE HOST SCHOOL :

     - to participate in activities of supporting the Headteacher and the   middle management staff ;

     - to  assist  the administration of national testing and inspections ;

     - to take part  in the drafting of the improvement plan based on the results of the assessment;

     - to participate in the activities of the governing bodies .

2 . EXCHANGE OF EXPERIENCES with foreign colleagues :

     - Participating in their activities

     - Discussion about  the strengths and weaknesses in  the local  assessment strategies.

Among the  particularly relevant results we include :

- knowledge and experience gained by the participants;

- improved cultural awareness;

- better  language skills ;

- improved  management skills and internationalization strategies;

- reinforced co-operation with partners from other countries.



The  expected impact on individual participants and  on the Institute  will be identified in the following:

           # DEVELOP AND MANAGE A TOOL FOR SELF-ASSESSMENT OF INSTITUTE

           # BUILD AN IMPROVEMENT PLAN  to reduce drift and improve student learning ( with particular emphasis on key skills ) .

May be considered as long-term benefits :

- the quality of an evaluation culture in the schools associated on the Net work  with the Comprehensive Institute;

- the contribution to the debate for the identification of new forms of organization and evaluation in school autonomy;

- motivating other public or private organisations  to participate in European Programmes.
